dvice:**\n   - All signal declarations use `logic`.\n   - The queue logic is placed within the same clock sensitivity block as the original error counting to ensure synchronous logging.\n   - The original complex XOR verification logic (`tb_match = ( { predict_taken_ref, predict_history_ref } === ( { predict_taken_ref, predict_history_ref } ^ { predict_taken_dut, predict_history_dut } ^ { predict_taken_ref, predict_history_ref } ) );`) is retained as it forms the basis of the reference check, even though the queue system now logs the mismatch.\n\n**Implementation Notes:**\n- The original testbench's `stats` struct and related variables are replaced by simple integer counters (`total_errors`, `first_error_time`) to integrate cleanly with the queue-based reporting.",
